race.description: Tab Same Race Multi Maiden Plate
race.comment: RUSKANA (5) debuts for Waterhouse-Bott and has been well educated. Has the blinkers on signalling intent, and expect her to have the early speed to skip across and ride the speed. Looks ready to go but the race day betting will tell plenty. ALAMAGAN (2) made good improvement here second-up when beaten 1.2 lengths over 1200m. Maps for the run of the race and is ready to win. ZOUSTRONG (1) drifted back and made ground fresh from a spell, finishing 2.2 lengths from the winner over 1200m at Kembla Grange. He's an improved gallop and fitter should be finishing hard. FIRE 'N' STONE (11) found one much too good over 1000m at Hawkesbury on debut, but covered the others. She has an awkward barrier but the longer sprint is sure to suit and she's sure to keep improving for a leading barn. ALABAMA HUSSY (6) has excuses last time but was on pace beaten 2L at Hawkesbury prior over this distance. Has the ability to feature.
